Name: Sev Poha
Description: Savory flattened rice flakes  cooked with vegetables and garnished with pomegranates and sev  along with in-house  Poha Masala..

Name: Kanchipuram idli
Description: Bringing you with most healthy breakfast recipe of idli. Made with  special rice and lentils this idli has choicest spices and is steamed and served with authentic. In house Kara  Dipping.

Name: Sev Usal
Description: a medley of sweet , tangy and spicy flavoured Peas curry , finest Indian spices garnished with sev and served with bun and our in-house dipping sauce.

Name: Surati Locho
Description: A surti delicacy made from gram dal with vey little oil and is steamed, served with spicy in-house  chutney, chilies and sev.

Name: Sev Khamani
Description: Traditional Surati Breakfast sev khamani is made from  chana dal or Bengal gram. The chana dal is crushed and stir fried with spices, chillies, ginger, garlic and saved with sev and Pomegranate seeds along with our in-house  Chutney.

Name: idli Sambhar
Description: Steamed rice and lentil cakes served over hot vegetable and lentil curry blended with choices spices from south India along with coconut and in-house tomato chutney.

Name: Samosa
Description: Very Prominent Triangle shaped  fried dumpling stuffed with mashed boiled potato, onions, green peas, spices and green chili and our secret samosa masala, served with 3 in-house dipping specialities.

Name: Vadapav
Description: Life line of Mumbai, Vada Pav is potato stuffing mixed with special masala, coated with gram flour and deep fried. It is served with bun , fried chillies and 3 in-house dipping specialities.

Name: dabeli
Description: Most famous Street food from Kutch province , this is a sandwich made with bun and potato  stuffing mixed with special in-house dabble masala , served with fried peanuts , sev , Pomegranates and 3 in-house dipping specialities.

Name: Puff
Description: most common tea time snack in India , puff pastry with vegetables / cheese stuffing baked and served with 3 in-house dipping specialities.

Name: Kachori
Description: out popular snack from  Rajasthan, India, Khasta Kachori is a crispy puff pastry deep fried with dry lentil stuffing  served with  3 in-house dipping specialities and sev

Name: samosa chaat
Description: Fresh crispy Samosa Crumbled and served with sev, chat  masala, yogurt,  fresh coriander , 3 in-house dipping specialities.

Name: Delhi Bhalla chaat
Description: Lentil dumplings  coated with yogurt, mint and coriander chutney, papdi and special dilli wali saunth.

Name: Dahi vada
Description: Lentil dumpling deep fried and served in yogurt and garnished with dilli special saints and seasoning

Name: Chutney puri
Description: Semolina puffed balls stuffed with boiled  potatoes and gram, onions, tomatoes garnished with coriander, sev , yogurt, chat masala and our 3 in- house dipping specialities

Name: Mumbai bhel
Description: A snack fro anytime hungry moments , a mix of puffed rice, sev, roasted spicy Hana dal, onion, tomato, green chili, raw mango , peanuts vanished with special in house bhel masala, lemon and cilantro

Name: dal vada
Description: : Lentil dumpling deep fried and served in yogurt and garnished with dilli special saints and seasoning

Name: Lassi
Description: yogurt blended with milk and water, sugar and served with cream, dry fruit and cherry topping , also available in mango flavor and slated option with cumin and  mint flavor.

Name: Falooda
Description:
A royal dessert made from mixing rose syrup, vermicelli, sweet basil (sabza/takmaria) seeds, and pieces of jelly with special thickened milk ,  topped off with a scoop of ice cream.

Various flavors like pista, kesar badam  are also available

Name: milk shakes
Description: Milk blend with fruits such as mango, banana , chiknoo saved with whipped cream and dry fruit garnish

Name: Bottle  soda
Description: special Indian soda to help with digestion.

Name: fresh juice
Description: fresh fruit and vegetables juice to keep you healthy
